fields.Dialogue Text: "Before you was only the room -- the sound of the motor vehicle. Steam in the bathroom. And darkness."

fields.Dialogue Text: She feeds herself another cigarette.

fields.Dialogue Text: "A lot of partying going on."

fields.Dialogue Text: You hear cracking in her shoulders.

fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess you can say that, yes. A bit. Lovers is such an emotional word. But there was something there. We did enough drugs for there to be."

fields.Dialogue Text: Air moves in your windpipe. Your heart beats. You're a detective -- get back to detecting.
